Johannesburg - Police on Monday requested the public to help find 40-year-old Guy Mclaughlin and 33-year-old Lindsay Lamb, who were both reported missing while on holiday in the Eastern Cape. "They were going to travel up to Hogsback and then proceed up the Wild Coast before leaving the province [to go] back to Gauteng. Information from relatives initially suggested that they left Grahamstown for Hogsback on Friday," said Captain Mali Govender.  "A vehicle matching the description was seen on the N2 on Friday travelling towards Butterworth by traffic officers conducting speed traps. There is a possibility that the couple may be along the Transkei coast."  The captain said the missing couple was driving a metallic brown Audi station wagon that had a bicycle on the roof. The registration number is RSM324GP. "Any person with information on the couple to contact their local police station or warrant officer, Andrew Bovey, of the Grahamstown South Africa Police Service on 0823019408," said Govender. African News Agency/ANA